The paper deals with learning the intrinsic structure of high-order tensors for object and face recognition, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper specifically mentions applications for object recognition and face recognition, which are commonly studied in the computer vision and machine learning communities. Therefore, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely categories, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.MM.
